<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>letterman • man of letters</xh5><p> <i>letterman</i>—(U.S.) a sportsman who has received some mark of distinction: He holds a Masters degree in Physical Education from the Citadel, where he was a three years <u>letterman</u> in football.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The compound does not correlate in meaning with <b>mailman</b>—a person who delivers letters, etc. or collects them from the letter-boxes: Our mail was delivered by the <u>mailman</u> who drove his car to every mail box along his assigned route.</p><p> <i>man of letters</i>—(formal) a scholar; a writer: To listen to the discoursing of an accomplished <u>man of letters</u> is always a pleasure.</p> </entry>
